description: A BJP booth president, Tapas Das, was arrested in Nandigram after a woman accused BJP supporters of assaulting her for switching to Trinamool. She claimed she was stripped and beaten, leading to her hospitalization. TMC has pledged support while BJP denies involvement, alleging a family dispute. Authorities are searching for other suspects.
title: West Bengal woman 'stripped, dragged on road'; BJP neta held

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi called for unity among Global South nations amid global uncertainties at the third Global South Summit hosted by India. He proposed a 'Global Development Compact' focused on sustainable growth without burdening countries with debt.
title: PM Modi proposes a new Global South deal without debt burden

description: Around 22 coaches of the Sabarmati Express derailed near Govindpuri station in Kanpur after hitting an object placed on the track, raising suspicions of sabotage. The incident occurred early Saturday, resulting in no injuries to passengers or staff. A committee has been formed for further investigation while train services were disrupted and restoration efforts commenced.
title: Probe launched as train hits object placed on track, derails

description: Authorities in Udaipur demolished a rented house after a Class 10 student was accused of stabbing a peer at a government school. In response to public outrage, officials suspended internet and closed schools. A medical team from Jaipur was flown in to treat the injured student, whose condition remains stable.
title: After stabbing, Raj asks teachers to check schoolbags for sharp objects
MBBS aspirant ends life after 2 failed NEET attempts
Woman killed by leopard, villagers halt train in protest

description: The Gujarat high court dismissed a petition by a judge removed for 'unsuitability' and suspected of forgery. Civil judge Mayuri Panchal's services were terminated due to unsatisfactory performance despite her attempts to contest the decision. Her anticipatory bail plea for alleged forgery was also rejected, but no action was pursued based on this allegation.
title: Gujarat HC upholds judge's dismissal for 'unsuitability'

description: A 31-year-old PG trainee doctor at RG Kar Hospital was raped and murdered after a 36-hour shift. Her body was discovered in the college's seminar room, sparking outrage and protests. The victim was hardworking, dreamed of becoming a gold medallist doctor, and was deeply cherished by her family and community.
title: Killed in own hospital: Doctor with a conscience who grew up in hardship

description: Karnataka governor Thaawar Chand Gehlot sanctioned prosecution against CM Siddaramaiah for the alleged Mysore Urban Development Authority land allotment scam. The opposition BJP and JD(S) called for Siddaramaiah's resignation. Siddaramaiah contested the governor's authority and vowed to fight it in court. The governor justified the decision, citing petitions from activists and supporting materials indicating offences.
title: Karnataka guv gives nod to prosecute Siddaramaiah in ‘land scam’

description: Haryana's BJP government made last-minute changes to SC and OBC quotas despite the model code of conduct being in effect. The cabinet meeting also included job security for certain contractual lecturers. CM Nayab Singh Saini expressed optimism about getting Election Commission approval for these decisions, although the opposition criticized the timing of these moves.
title: Haryana okays sops day after poll date; subject to EC’s nod, says CM

description: In a significant setback for the Jannayak Janata Party (JJP), four MLAs resigned within 24 hours. The departures come after BJP severed ties, ousting JJP from power in March. This leaves Dushyant Chautala with support from only three MLAs. The resignations cite personal reasons and suggest shifting alliances ahead of the Haryana Assembly elections.
title: Polls trigger exodus in Dushyant's JJP: 4 MLAs leave party in 24 hours
Home minister Amit Shah confident of winning all state polls

description: Congress urged the National Conference (NC) and the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) to form a wider alliance in Jammu and Kashmir assembly polls to defeat the BJP. Congress general secretary Ghulam Ahmad Mir emphasized unity, citing the earlier collaboration as the People's Alliance for Gupkar Declaration, and criticized them for not staying united during the Lok Sabha elections.
title: J&K polls: Cong urges NC & PDP to form broad alliance against BJP

description: The Election Commission announced that assembly polls in Maharashtra will be declared only after the results for J&K and Haryana on October 4. The Maharashtra and Jharkhand elections are expected to be conducted in November, prior to the expiration of the Maharashtra assembly's term on November 26. The decision considered logistical and expenditure factors.
title: Maharashtra assembly polls likely in November
Earthquake of magnitude 7.2 hits Russia's Kamchatka
TMC fires ex-MP Shantanu as Kolkata civic body adviser
CBI to conduct layered voice analysis test on RG Kar accused

description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah can consider challenging the governor's decision in the high court, with an option to escalate to the Supreme Court. Despite legal troubles over MUDA site allotment scam, his position remained strong with party support. Past instances, like Yediyurappa's case, indicated possible non-resignation. The special court's outcome will be crucial in determining proceedings.
title: Siddaramaiah has option of challenging in court guv's sanction for prosecution

description: The Maharashtra government's Mukhyamantri Ladki Bahin scheme faced a hiccup when funds intended for women ended up in a man's account. Jaffar Sheikh of Yavatmal unexpectedly received Rs 3,000. Authorities acknowledged the error, affecting many women struggling to link their Aadhaar with bank accounts. The complaint has been forwarded for further investigation.
title: Ladki Bahin money lands in Maharashtra man's account

description: Kolkata police described the vandalisation of RG Kar hospital on August 14-15 as premeditated, arresting 30 individuals so far. Attackers traveled in groups from various city areas. Police linked the incident to organized protests and specific WhatsApp groups. Police have formed 10 raid teams to apprehend suspects and investigate their connections further.
title: Cops say hospital rampage premeditated, 30 arrested
New panels set up, Congress MP Venugopal to head PAC

description: The West Bengal government revoked the transfer of 42 doctors within 24 hours of its issuance following intervention by chief minister Mamata Banerjee. Allegations suggested the transfers targeted faculty members who protested against the rape and murder of a trainee doctor.
title: Bengal transfers 42 doctors, revokes order within 24 hours

description: Mukesh Ambani continued his zero-salary policy for the fourth straight year in FY24, initially made in response to the Covid-19 pandemic. While Ambani forwent his pay, other top Reliance executives, including his cousins Nikhil and Hital Meswani, saw increases in their remuneration.
title: Mukesh Ambani continues this 'Covid times salary trend'

description: The CBI's extensive interrogation of Sandip Ghosh, former principal of RG Kar Medical College, continued for over 23 hours regarding the alleged rape-murder of a 31-year-old doctor. The inquiry followed complaints from the victim's parents about workplace pressure and a suspected cover-up. Several hospital staff and colleagues were also questioned to clarify the events surrounding the death.
title: 23 hours & counting: RG Kar ex-principal faces CBI heat
PDP, NC positive reactions to J&K polls signal shift in stand
‘Rattirer Shaathi’, restrooms: Bengal lists safety measures for women docs
London shocker: Intruder attacks Air India air hostess in her hotel room near Heathrow

description: Elon Musk's social media platform X ceased operations in Brazil due to censorship orders from Judge Alexandre de Moraes. X claimed Moraes threatened one of its legal representatives with arrest unless they complied. This follows earlier orders to block accounts linked to spreading fake news and hate messages during former President Jair Bolsonaro's term.
title: 'Censorship dispute': Elon Musk's X to close operations in Brazil

description: Former J&K minister Taj Mohiuddin announced his resignation from the Democratic Progressive Azad Party (DPAP) and his return to the Congress. He stated that his workers advised the move. "My workers asked me to rejoin the Congress, so I decided to leave the DPAP and rejoin the Congress," he said. With assembly elections on the horizon, he expressed readiness to contest if granted a ticket by Congress.
title: 'Ghar Wapsi': Taj Mohiuddin leaves DPAP, to rejoin Congress

description: Shepard Fairey, known for the Obama 'hope' poster, released a similar Kamala Harris 'progress' poster for the current election. His endorsement of Harris and her running mate Tim Walz contrasts his past disappointment with Obama and refusal to support Clinton or Biden. Fairey found inspiration in Harris's campaign message: 'We are not going back.'
title: 'Hope' and 'progress' in America as Donald Trump totters
Andhra CM Naidu meets PM Modi; discusses state's financial situation
Bangladesh’s ousted PM Sheikh Hasina faces seventh murder case charges

description: Dinesh Karthik was mistaken for Bollywood actor Vikrant Massey by a fan who praised his "performance" in Massey's film "Phir Aayi Haseen Dilruba" on social media. Karthik humorously responded with a lighthearted, "Oh wow!!! Thanks," showing his wit. This playful interaction quickly gained attention, adding to Karthik's recent buzz.
title: Fan mistakes Dinesh Karthik for ‘12th Fail’ actor, gets hilarious reply
Elephant shooed away using spiked rods, fireball before dying
'Uddhav is ready to support, but ... ': Sanjay Raut on MVA's CM candidate in Maharashtra

description: Donald Trump enlisted former Democratic lawmaker Tulsi Gabbard to help him prepare for a debate against Kamala Harris. The move aimed to structure his campaign and regain support amid erratic behavior and declining poll numbers. Gabbard, aligned with Trump's views on national security, had clashed with Harris in a 2019 debate.
title: Why Trump chose Tulsi Gabbard for debate prep against Kamala Harris

description: Mike Francesa criticised the New York Mets' decision to invite Hailey Welch for the first pitch at their game against the Oakland A's. Welch, known for a viral controversial remark, was invited on a camp day with young fans attending. Francesa questioned the team's marketing decision and speculated on possible repercussions for those responsible.
title: 'Imagine explaining his wife': Mike Francesa slams Mets for 'Hawk Tuah Girl' first pitch

description: Residents of Palmdale and Lancaster, California, reported UFO sightings, sharing their experiences on the Ring Neighbors app. Local authorities have started investigating these intriguing claims. One resident described seeing a shooting star that zig-zagged in the sky. The sightings have sparked curiosity and discussions in the community. Authorities are looking into the validity of these reported sightings.
title: UFO sightings in Palmdale and Lancaster, California: Local residents share experiences on Ring Neighbors app

description: In a press release addressed to Prime Minister Narendra Modi, the IMA outlined a series of solutions and demands aimed at addressing the deep-seated vulnerabilities that the tragedy has exposed. "Doctors especially women are vulnerable to violence because of the nature of the profession. It is for the authorities to provide for the safety of doctors inside hospitals and campuses," the press release said.​​
title: Kolkata rape-murder: IMA writes to PM Modi, lists series of demands for safety of doctors
'Hum jahan par hain ...': Champai Soren on joining BJP rumors

description: The resignation of Sheikh Hasina as Bangladesh's Prime Minister amid widespread protests has led to significant unrest, with over 600 deaths reported. Nobel laureate Muhammad Yunus heads the interim government, but questions about stability remain. Comparisons with Afghanistan and Pakistan are discussed, as student leaders take on governance roles, highlighting future uncertainties in the nation.
title: Bangladesh after Sheikh Hasina: Will it become next Afghanistan or Pakistan?

description: A young girl has taken the internet by storm with her impressive imitation of Jasprit Bumrah's unique bowling action. The video, which has gone viral on social media, shows the girl perfectly replicating his signature style while bowling in the nets.
title: In viral video, young girl tries to emulate Bumrah's action

description: A fire broke out at Somerset House, central London, with around 125 firefighters and 20 fire engines controlling the blaze. The fire affected the building's roof, although artworks were safe. The London Fire Brigade said: "20 fire engines and around 125 firefighters have now been sent in response to the fire at Somerset House. Crews are tackling a fire located in part of the building's roof."
title: Fire at Somerset House where Van Gogh and Cezanne Art is displayed

description: Controversy erupted in Pakistan after a gala dinner honouring Olympic javelin champion Arshad Nadeem saw former hockey Olympians' invitations rescinded last minute due to "guest management" issues. Rao Saleem Nazim, a former Olympian, revealed that numerous hockey legends were initially invited by the Prime Minister’s House but were later informed their invitations were withdrawn. The incident has sparked outrage among the athletes, who view it as disrespectful, questioning the disregard for Pakistan’s historic hockey achievements while celebrating Nadeem’s success.
title: Controversy mars Nadeem's gala dinner as Govt cancels invitations

description: ​​The trauma care cubes, which have been developed indigenously under Project BHISHM (Bharat Health Initiative for Sahyog Hita and Maitri), are crucial for providing critical medical assistance in remote areas.
title: Watch: IAF & Army para-drop world's 1st portable hosp at 15,000 feet
Tackling illicit financial flows – a key area for UN’s tax framework

description: UP Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath criticized the previous Samajwadi Party government, citing malpractices in recruitments, while distributing over 2,500 appointment letters in Ambedkar Nagar. He asserted that such corruption would not be tolerated. Additionally, Adityanath announced a 20 percent quota for women in police recruitment and distributed loans and tablets at the event.
title: 'Chacha-bhatija and goons went for...' : UP CM Yogi slams Samajwadi Party

description: Union Health Minister JP Nadda reviewed India's monkeypox preparedness, implementing measures at airports, seaports, and crossings to detect and manage potential cases. While monkeypox usually lasts 2-4 weeks and has low risk of large outbreaks, authorities are vigilant, especially concerning African arrivals. A serosurvey is being conducted to understand the infection risk among high-risk groups.
title: 'Risk of large outbreak low': Centre reviews Monkeypox situation in country

description: Neeraj Chopra, who won silver medal at Paris Olympics, said he couldn't push himself to his extreme.Chopra fell short of retaining his gold medal in the men's javelin throw at the ongoing marquee event securing silver with a best throw of 89.45 meters. Speaking at a virtual press briefing, Neeraj said that mentally he was ready but lacked in the physical area.
title: 'My throw immediately after Arshad Nadeem's throw was ... ': Neeraj Chopra

description: A political clash erupted between Congress and BJP after Karnataka governor Thaawarchand Gehlot allowed the prosecution of CM Siddaramaiah over the alleged Mysuru Urban Development Authority (MUDA) scam. Congress leaders defended Siddaramaiah, asserting the move as a conspiracy. Meanwhile, BJP demanded Siddaramaiah's resignation for a fair investigation. The Karnataka government plans to challenge the governor's decision in court.
title: Sanction for prosecution: CM Siddaramaiah rules out resignation; BJP hits back

description: Deeptech startup Saarthi.ai faced significant issues last year, failing to pay overdue salaries and reducing its workforce by over 70%. The company also did not remit TDS for two fiscal years.
title: After laying off 70% employees, CEO claims not able to go to US to...
